{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "3ddc9ef6",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# FVS five-county Florida growth smoke run\n",
    "\n",
    "Goal: grow a small deterministic set of TreeMap/FIA stands from the Baker/Columbia/Hamilton/Suwannee/Union County AOI with FVS Southern (`SN`).\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook is intentionally a smoke-run harness, not the final trajectory-library builder. It:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. probes local FVS shared libraries under `FVS/`,\n",
    "2. selects 10 FVS-ready stands from the existing consolidated SQLite DB,\n",
    "3. writes no-management keyfiles for Linux/WSL and Windows FVS,\n",
    "4. optionally tries the local Linux `FVSsn.so` path, and\n",
    "5. summarizes any output SQLite DBs that FVS produces.\n",
    "\n",
    "Known current result: the local Linux `FVS/fvs-modern/lib/FVSsn.so` library loads, but DB-backed projections segfault in this environment after `OPEN FAILED FOR 17 ... unrecognized token: \"'\"`. The generated Windows keyfiles are therefore the safer handoff for running through the installed graphical FVS at `C:\\FVS`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "92783a25",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from __future__ import annotations\n",
    "\n",
    "import csv\n",
    "import re\n",
    "import shutil\n",
    "import sqlite3\n",
    "import subprocess\n",
    "import sys\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "\n",
    "PROJECT_ROOT = Path.cwd()\n",
    "if PROJECT_ROOT.name == \"notebooks\":\n",
    "    PROJECT_ROOT = PROJECT_ROOT.parent\n",
    "sys.path.insert(0, str(PROJECT_ROOT))\n",
    "\n",
    "from pipeline.s4_fvs.keyword_builder import (\n",
    "    select_smoke_stands,\n",
    "    write_smoke_keyfiles,\n",
    ")\n",
    "from pipeline.s4_fvs.probe_libraries import probe_variant_libraries\n",
    "from pipeline.s4_fvs.run_smoke import add_fvs2py_path, run_manifest, write_status\n",
    "from pipeline.s4_fvs.summarize_smoke import summarize_manifest, summarize_output_db, write_summary\n",
    "\n",
    "INPUT_DB = Path(\"/mnt/d/TreeMap_Chaz/output2020/FIA_5county_consolidated.db\")\n",
    "LINUX_OUT_DIR = PROJECT_ROOT / \"data/interim/fvs/smoke_no_management\"\n",
    "WINDOWS_OUT_DIR = Path(\"/mnt/d/TreeMap_Chaz/artemis_fvs_smoke_no_management\")\n",
    "WINDOWS_FVS_OUTPUT_DB = Path(\"/mnt/c/FVS/Artemis_project/FVSOut.db\")\n",
    "FVS_LIB = PROJECT_ROOT / \"FVS/fvs-modern/lib/FVSsn.so\"\n",
    "FVS2PY_PATH = PROJECT_ROOT / \"FVS/fvs2py\"\n",
    "\n",
    "LIMIT = 10\n",
    "INPUT_LEVEL = \"plot\"  # plot matches the previous successful-looking Windows FVS run\n",
    "RUN_LOCAL_FVS = False  # set True only when you want to test the Linux shared-library path\n",
    "\n",
    "# With RUN_LOCAL_FVS = False, summarize/load the Windows FVS output database.\n",
    "# Windows path: C:\\FVS\\Artemis_project\\FVSOut.db\n",
    "# WSL path:     /mnt/c/FVS/Artemis_project/FVSOut.db\n",
    "# If you run FVS locally through fvs2py instead, set RUN_LOCAL_FVS = True.\n",
    "FVS_OUTPUT_MANIFEST = None\n",
    "DUCKDB_TABLE = \"fvs_summary2\"\n",
    "START_DUCKDB_UI = True  # set False if running headless or inside nbconvert/CI\n",
    ""
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "307dfc0b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Probe local FVS libraries\n",
    "\n",
    "Only `SN` is appropriate for this Florida AOI. The all-variant probe can be run from the shell with:\n",
    "\n",
    "```bash\n",
    "uv run python -m pipeline.s4_fvs.probe_libraries --variant all --check-fvs2py --out-csv data/interim/fvs/library_probe.csv\n",
    "```\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "db851dde",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
