  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "6d9bb7ee",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Optional local Linux FVS run\n",
    "\n",
    "The isolated subprocess mode is deliberate: current `FVSsn.so` experiments can segfault. Leaving `RUN_LOCAL_FVS = False` keeps the notebook safe by default."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "bd8dc304",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Skipped local FVS run. Set RUN_LOCAL_FVS = True to test FVSsn.so.\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "if RUN_LOCAL_FVS:\n",
    "    add_fvs2py_path(FVS2PY_PATH)\n",
    "    status_rows = run_manifest(\n",
    "        linux_manifest,\n",
    "        fvs_lib=FVS_LIB,\n",
    "        fvs2py_path=FVS2PY_PATH,\n",
    "        limit=3,\n",
    "        isolate_subprocess=True,\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    status_csv = LINUX_OUT_DIR / \"run_status.csv\"\n",
    "    write_status(status_csv, status_rows)\n",
    "    display(pd.DataFrame(status_rows))\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"Skipped local FVS run. Set RUN_LOCAL_FVS = True to test FVSsn.so.\")\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f6fc8fad",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Summarize FVS output\n",
    "\n",
    "With `RUN_LOCAL_FVS = False`, this notebook reads the Windows FVS output SQLite database at `C:\\FVS\\Artemis_project\\FVSOut.db` (`/mnt/c/FVS/Artemis_project/FVSOut.db` from WSL). The generated `FVS_Data.db` is the project/input database; `FVSOut.db` contains `FVS_Cases`, `FVS_Summary2`, and `FVS_Error`. The manifest-based per-stand SQLite output path remains the fallback for local Linux/fvs2py runs."
   ]
  },
